The paper deals with the approximability of a graph problem (maximum edge-disjoint paths) and the integrality gap of its natural multicommodity flow based relaxation. This suggests that it belongs to the category of "Data Structures and Algorithms" (cs.DS). The paper also considers the problem in the context of planar graphs and bounded genus graphs, which are topics related to "Graph Theory" (cs.GT) and "Computational Geometry" (cs.CG), respectively. The paper also presents a polytime algorithm for a graph of bounded treewidth, which falls under the category of "Numerical Analysis" (cs.NA). Finally, the paper discusses the properties of graph families, which is a topic related to "Discrete Mathematics" (cs.DM).
